mething like this:","provider.flow.microsoft_365.card_1.content.sentence_1":"Go to the <textbutton>Domains page</textbutton> at Microsoft 365 and log in","provider.flow.microsoft_365.card_3.content.sentence_1":"Head back to Microsoft and click <bold>\u201cVerify\u201d</bold>","provider.flow.microsoft_365.card_1.title":"1. Add your domain to Microsoft 365","provider.flow.microsoft_365.card_1.cta.sentence_2":"Head to the Microsoft 365 admin center and open the side menu. Under <bold>\u201cShow All\u201d</bold> go to <bold>\u201cSettings\u201d</bold> and choose <bold>\u201cDomains.\u201d</bold>","provider.flow.microsoft_365.card_3.content.sentence_4":"You\u2019ll know you\u2019re finished with setup when you get a message from Microsoft 365 that <bold>\u201cDomain setup is complete.\u201d</bold>","provider.flow.godaddy.card_2.content.sentence_1":"Go through the <bold>\\"1. Select domain,\\" \\"2. Create account,\\"</bold> steps until you reach step <bold>\\"3. Validate domain\\"</bold> where you\u2019ll see a list of DNS records","provider.flow.cta.sentence_4":"Note: In rare cases, it may take up to an hour for your domain settings to update.","provider.flow.godaddy.card_2.validation.message":"To save your value, make sure it begins with \u201dMS=ms\u201d or \u201dD\u201d","provider.flow.godaddy.card_2.content.cta":"You\u2019ll need to add your DNS records from {providerName} to your domain settings at Wix. \\n<bold>Some of the records were already added automatically:</bold>","provider.flow.godaddy.card_1.content.sentence_3":"Add your domain name <bold>{domainName}</bold> and then continue to the next step at {providerName}","provider.flow.other.card_1.content.sentence_3":"Add your domain <bold>{domainName}</bold> to begin setting up your email. <div>If you\u2019ve already added it, find your domain name and begin setup.</div>","provider.flow.tier2.card_1.content.sentence_1":"Log in to your {providerName} account","provider.flow.cta.sentence_1":"If your domain is not 